25/11/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Parliamentary Assembly of the Council of Europe President Rene van Der Linden urged Romania Thursday (24 November) to take tougher action on corruption and human trafficking. In an address to the Romanian Parliament, Van Der Linden said corruption had led to a loss of confidence in public institutions and threatens foreign investments. He called for independent judges and a reformed public administration. Van Der Linden met with President Traian Basescu, Senate Speaker Nicolae Vacaroiu and the head of Romanian Orthodox Church, Patriarch Teoctist. (Nine O'clock - 25/11/04; Rompres, CoE website - 24/11/05)
